1. IRIS — Person-State Response Router (`src/core/iris.js`)

What it is: The world's first person-state matched response router. Before responding, IRIS asks "who is this person, what state are they in, and what response architecture serves them best?"

Why Omo-Koda2 needs it: Currently Omo-Koda2 has rigid `think`/`act` primitives with hermetic scoring but no adaptive response depth. IRIS would sit between the Steward's intent compilation and the LLM provider call.

Porting strategy: Extract the routing logic into a Rust module `omokoda-core/src/iris/mod.rs`.

```rust
// omokoda-core/src/iris/mod.rs
use crate::session::SessionState;
use crate::identity::AgentId;

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub enum ResponseProfile {
    Reflex,    // instant, one line
    Fast,      // direct, 2-3 lines
    Balanced,  // clear and complete
    Deep,      // thorough, full depth
    Gentle,    // high tension — soften, slow down
    Sharp,     // debugging, code — accuracy over warmth
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct IrisRouting {
    pub profile: ResponseProfile,
    pub max_tokens: u32,
    pub temperature: f32,
    pub style_injection: String,
    pub warmth_boost: bool,
    pub reasoning: String,
}

pub struct IrisEngine;

impl IrisEngine {
    pub fn route(
        message: &str,
        session: &SessionState,
        lpm: &Option<LifelongPersonalModel>,
    ) -> IrisRouting {
        // 1. Classify query type
        let base = classify_query(message);
        
        // 2. Apply emotional overrides from session state
        let emotion = session.emotion_state();
        let mut final_profile = base;
        
        if emotion.tension > 0.6 && !matches!(base, ResponseProfile::Sharp | ResponseProfile::Reflex) {
            final_profile = ResponseProfile::Gentle;
        }
        if emotion.energy < 0.3 && matches!(final_profile, ResponseProfile::Deep) {
            final_profile = ResponseProfile::Balanced;
        }
        if emotion.focus > 0.7 && matches!(final_profile, ResponseProfile::Balanced) {
            final_profile = ResponseProfile::Deep;
        }
        
        // 3. LPM-based personalization
        if let Some(lpm) = lpm {
            if lpm.prefers_short && matches!(final_profile, ResponseProfile::Deep) {
                final_profile = ResponseProfile::Balanced;
            }
            if lpm.prefers_depth && matches!(final_profile, ResponseProfile::Fast) {
                final_profile = ResponseProfile::Balanced;
            }
            // Foresight matching
            if lpm.foresight.iter().any(|f| message.to_lowercase().contains(&f.to_lowercase())) {
                if matches!(final_profile, ResponseProfile::Reflex | ResponseProfile::Fast) {
                    final_profile = ResponseProfile::Balanced;
                }
            }
        }
        
        final_profile.into_routing()
    }
}
